headlines.description: — Coby White narrowly missed his first career triple-double, finishing with 23 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists, and Torrey Craig scored 18 with five 3-pointers after halftime as the Chicago Bulls held on to beat the Charlotte Hornets 115-108 in...
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White, Torrey Craig lead the Bulls past the Hornets in overtime, 115-108

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Josh Hart had 23 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists for his third triple-double of the season, Karl-Anthony Towns had 32 points and 13 rebounds, and the New York Knicks beat the Washington Wizards 126-106 on Monday night for their eighth straight...
headlines.shortLinkText: Hart's triple-double, Towns' 32 points lead Knicks to 8th straight win, 126-106 over Wizards

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 35 points, James Harden hit go-ahead free throws with 17.9 seconds left and the Los Angeles Clippers held on to defeat the New Orleans Pelicans 116-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell and Harden lift the Clippers to a 116-113 comeback victory over the skidding Pelicans

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook became the second player in NBA history to have a triple-double with zero turnovers and shoot 100% from the field and the free-throw line in the Denver Nuggets' 132-121 win...
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook has 'perfect' triple-double, 0 turnovers in Nuggets' 132-121 win over Jazz

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 25 points, Donovan Mitchell scored 23 and the Cleveland Cavaliers extended their winning streak to seven games with a 113-95 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cleveland extends winning streak to 7 games with 113-95 win over Golden State

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 37 points and nine rebounds as the Philadelphia 76ers defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 125-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 37 as 76ers handle Trail Blazes 125-103

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 33 points, and the Sacramento Kings beat the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 110-100 on Monday night to give Doug Christie his first win...
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox has 33 points, Kings beat Mavericks 110-100 as Christie wins first after becoming interim coach
